CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 18, 1961, page 19, reads: "GOP Dinner - When Allegheny County Republicans stages their Lincoln dinner on Feb. 11, Governor John A. Volpe of Massachusetts, while president John F. Kennedy was sweeping the state by more than half-a-million votes. Governor Volpe (center) is shown chatting with Commissioner John M. Walker (left). Looking on are the Rev. LeRoy Patrick (standing left) and William P. Young (right). - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Commissioner John M. Walker holding book, Rev. LeRoy Patrick, Massachusetts Governor John A. Volpe and William P. Young standing in interior for Allegheny County Republican Lincoln Dinner
